last_episode_to_air.name: Just Let It Go
last_episode_to_air.overview: As the Busby's head to Disney World, Danielle is determined to turn off work mode and focus on having fun. Things get tricky for Adam when a job opprotunity comes up forcing the Busbys to debate their priorities.

name: OutDaughtered
overview: 40 bottles a day, 420 diapers a week and feedings every three hours became the new normal for Danielle and Adam Busby when they welcomed home the only all-female set of quintuplets in the country. The family of three became a family of eight overnight, and TLC follows that incredible journey in the new series "OUTDAUGHTERED". The series captures Danielle, Adam and their adorable 4-year-old daughter Blayke as they adjust to their new life, while trying to hold on to the identities and lives they had cultivated before the five new additions arrived. Following the hilarious and heartwarming antics of the entire family including Danielle's zany mother, Michelle, and her older twin sisters and their families, it's all hands on deck as the family relies on their tight-knit circle to make the most out of this incredible lifetime adventure.

episodes.name: Make Room for Quints
episodes.overview: Adam and Danielle Busby defy all odds by giving birth to the first set of all girl quintuplets in the US. After four months in the NICU, the quints come home and along with four-year-old sister Blayke, turn Adam and Danielle's lives upside down.

episodes.name: Chaos with Quints
episodes.overview: Adam and Danielle struggle to keep up with the demands of the quintuplets while also making time for 4-year-old daughter, Blayke. Later, a baby photo shoot with the quints turns into pure chaos when Grandma Mimi shows up late to help.

episodes.name: Quintuple Trouble
episodes.overview: Adam returns to work, leaving Danielle to care for the quintuplets and Blayke by herself for the first time. On Adam's first day back, Hazel falls ill with a fever, leaving the family scrambling and Danielle feeling overwhelmed and alone.

episodes.name: Should We Stay or Should We Go?
episodes.overview: Adam & Danielle realize they need a larger home, but house hunting proves stressful when they realize what a larger house will cost. Later, the family heads back to their hometown & Danielle comes up with an idea that could solve all their problems.

episodes.name: Catching Up with the Quints
episodes.overview: The Busbys are back & life is more chaotic than ever! Adam & Danielle have their hands full chasing after their 15 month old quints. And when a doctor recommends an extreme medical procedure for one of the girls, the Busbys face a difficult decision.

episodes.name: All Eyes on Hazel
episodes.overview: The Busbys take a road trip to help Mimi with her garage sale, but Danielle is shocked by news from her mom. Meanwhile, Adam and Danielle discuss a recommended eye surgery for Hazel.

episodes.name: A Quint in Crisis
episodes.overview: Hazel undergoes eye surgery, causing Adam and Danielle to wait anxiously for the results; Blayke prepares for kindergarten and Mimi officially moves in.

episodes.name: Quint-Fluenza
episodes.overview: When Danielle catches the flu, Mimi struggles to take care of 5 babies on her own. Adam plans a 10-year anniversary surprise for Danielle. Later, when Danielle gives a speech for the hospital, she faces the painful past of having premature babies.

episodes.name: This Little Quint Stays Home
episodes.overview: Danielle and Adam explore sending the quints to nursery school, but when one of the them isn't allowed to go, the Busbys face the difficult decision of splitting the girls up. As for Mimi, living under the Busby roof has begun to take a serious toll.

episodes.name: 5 Babies on a Budget
episodes.overview: After Danielle confronts Adam about his money spending ways, they realize they need to make some tough choices to provide for their six girls. They also continue to step up their efforts to get Hazel walking so she can join her sisters in pre-school.

episodes.name: A Nightmare on Quint Street
episodes.overview: It's Halloween, but before the Busbys can celebrate the Quints' first trick-or-treat outing, they have to find costumes, shop for pumpkins and get the new house ready for a Halloween party, all while making a final decision on a $100,000 investment.

episodes.name: Quint-cation Chaos
episodes.overview: It's the quints' first family vacation! But with five toddlers running wild, it may feel more like work than vacation time for Adam and Danielle. Meanwhile, Adam struggles to tell his brother-in-law, and boss, about the new business he's starting.

episodes.name: A Thanksgiving Miracle
episodes.overview: It's Thanksgiving at the Busby household! Adam & Danielle decide to host 20 people but soon realize they have bitten off more than they can chew. Meanwhile, Hazel has a major breakthrough and Adam & Danielle push Mimi to consider apartment living.

episodes.name: The Quints Take Manhattan
episodes.overview: When a talk show asks the Busbys to make a live TV appearance in New York, the family heads to the Big Apple. But traveling with 6 kids is as difficult as it sounds! And a last-minute trip to the doctor has Danielle and Adam concerned about Hazel.

episodes.name: Dawn of the Terrible Twos
episodes.overview: With the quints hitting the 'terrible twos," the Busbys are busier than ever; Danielle plans a romantic Valentine's Day dinner for Adam, but things don't go as planned; Adam and Danielle prepare themselves for Hazel's upcoming eye appointment.

episodes.name: A Little Potty Never Killed Nobody
episodes.overview: With the possibility of another surgery looming for Hazel, Adam stresses over her upcoming appointment with a new doctor; when the quints start having poop explosions, Daniel tries potty training with disastrous results.

episodes.name: Good Quints Gone Bad
episodes.overview: The Busbys tackle discipline to get the terrible twos under control; Danielle presses Adam for answers on how he's been feeling; with Mimi taking her time to move into her new home, Danielle devises a plan to help her embrace her new life.

episodes.name: Extreme Quint Makeover
episodes.overview: While Adam struggles with his emotional issues, the Busbys tackle a playroom makeover for the quints and Blayke; Hazel gets fitted for her new glasses just in time for the girls to take the stage for their first recital.

episodes.name: Multiple Births, Multiple Birthdays
episodes.overview: The Busbys plan a joint birthday party for all their girls, but when Blayke wants her own party Adam and Danielle must come up with a way to make her feel special. The quints' turning 2 also means it's time for their first trip to the dentist.

episodes.name: The Nightmare Before Easter
episodes.overview: It's Easter time and the Busbys have tons of fun activities planned for the holiday, but their special surprise may turn into a nightmare. Also, when Adam reveals his unorthodox plan for dealing with his issues, Danielle has a tough decision to make

episodes.name: While the Busbys Are Away the Quints Will Play
episodes.overview: Adam and Danielle take a trip to Nashville, leaving Danielle’s family to watch the quints, but they may not be up to the challenge when Hazel gives her uncle a big scare. While they’re away, Adam realizes he’s not the only one suffering from his issues.

episodes.name: Battle of the Busby Baby Photos
episodes.overview: Adam and Danielle compete to see who can take the cutest photo of the quints so they can promote the new cycle studio; Danielle stresses about her upcoming charity fundraiser; Adam takes a big step toward dealing with his emotional issues.

episodes.name: Mother's Day Getaway
episodes.overview: In an enhanced episode, Adam plans a beach vacation getaway for Mother's Day, but it might be more chaos than calm with the entire extended family in tow. On the trip, the quints see the ocean for the first time, and Adam reveals his struggles to Nick and Dale.

episodes.name: The Busby's Newest Addition
episodes.overview: With the grand opening of the cycle studio looming, tensions rise when Danielle announces she wants to work there more than expected; Hazel returns to the eye doctor; the quints get invited to be grand marshals of the League City parade.

episodes.name: The Quints Have Taken Over!
episodes.overview: A family member suffers a devastating loss when Hurricane Harvey hits; Danielle and Adam are split on what to do about Olivia escaping from her crib; and Danielle may have to work through the fun when it’s time for the simple pleasures of Halloween.

episodes.name: A Very Busby Thanksgiving
episodes.overview: The Busbys plan a special Thanksgiving, but bad news for Mimi may throw the holiday into turmoil. When Adam and Danielle find out that Riley and Parker are moving up to a different classroom, Adam struggles with the idea of separating the quints.

episodes.name: It's My Potty and I'll Cry If I Want To
episodes.overview: The Busbys wade back into potty training, determined not to be defeated this time. Blayke takes gymnastics lessons & enjoys one-on-one time with her parents. Mimi distances herself from the family as she struggles with the loss of her house.

episodes.name: When Danielle's Away, the Quints Will Play
episodes.overview: Adam’s left in charge of all six kids for the weekend, as Danielle goes out of town for a work conference. Even though parenting solo is overwhelming, he has big plans in store for his little ladies. A routine eye checkup for Hazel delivers shocking news.

episodes.name: It's Beginning to Look a Lot like Quintmas
episodes.overview: Danielle and Adam want to give their daughters the best Christmas, but as their plans crumble, so does Danielle.

episodes.name: I'm Dreaming of a Cajun Christmas
episodes.overview: Blayke hopes to turn a profit with her business; Danielle's stress gets worse; Adam reveals the truth about his vasectomy.

episodes.name: New Year, New Responsibilities
episodes.overview: Danielle begins the new year by making a chore chart to teach the kids to help around the house, but wonders if this will remedy her exhaustion or double the quints' tantrums; the girls enter a fashion show.

episodes.name: The Last Time This Happened We Had Quints!
episodes.overview: As Danielle's health concerns grow, Adam reveals a bombshell secret that could mean she's actually pregnant; the couple's stress skyrockets when one of the quints goes missing; Blayke opens a lemonade stand and the entire family is ready to help.

episodes.name: OutValentined
episodes.overview: Adam faces the challenge of pleasing his wife and all six of his daughters for Valentine’s Day. Later, Adam and Danielle are stunned by what they learn at Hazel’s doctor appointment.

episodes.name: Houston, We Have a Potty Problem
episodes.overview: Danielle is ready to get the girls into underwear, but Adam is worried; Mimi asks to meet up with Danielle.

episodes.name: Every Quint for Herself
episodes.overview: Adam and Danielle hope teaching the quints to share will stop their constant fighting; Blayke has a gymnastics evaluation but one wrong step may cost her the chance to move up; the Busbys step in to help a family hurt by the hurricane.

episodes.name: Busby Birthday Bash
episodes.overview: The Busbys throw a joint birthday party for the girls, but Danielle also plans individual birthday outings! When Adam's job causes him to miss out on the fun, he faces a big decision. A familiar guest scares the girls at the Busby Easter celebration.

episodes.name: Hawaii Five-Uh-Oh
episodes.overview: The Busbys head to Hawaii! But it's trouble in paradise as the quints have constant meltdowns and Riley gets lost. Danielle and Adam face a tough decision as his desire to quit his job grows. Hazel returns to the eye doctor with surgery looming.

episodes.name: Young, Wild & Three
episodes.overview: The quints are full-blown threenagers now, and Danielle and Adam must figure out how to make them more disciplined; Adam tries to balance working from home, but after Ava gets sick, the Busbys make a shocking discovery in their house.

episodes.name: Our Home Is Sick
episodes.overview: The quints have their first sleepover at the Mills when the Busbys are forced to leave their home for a few days.

episodes.name: The Quints Get Schooled
episodes.overview: Thanksgiving is right around the corner, but celebrating is the last thing on the Busbys' minds; tensions run high between Adam and Danielle as they continue the hunt for a new house and the quints undergo their first school testing.

episodes.name: New House, New Problems
episodes.overview: The Busbys move out of their mold-infested home, but transitioning isn't easy; the quints night time antics escalate until Adam and Danielle split up their bedrooms for the first time; Adam plans a surprise birthday party for Danielle.

episodes.name: The Nightmare Before Quintmas
episodes.overview: As the Busbys navigate life in their new home, Adam and Danielle try to salvage what's left of the Christmas season; when Danielle learns she needs surgery on her wisdom teeth, Adam struggles to keep the house afloat and deliver a perfect Christmas.

episodes.name: Lights, Camera, Quints!
episodes.overview: Adam gets a great work opportunity, but he needs to rely on the chaotic quints to make it a success; when Parker's anxiety gets the best of her, the Busbys must look for solutions; Blayke follows in her mom's footsteps with a new hobby.

episodes.name: Quints on the high seas
episodes.overview: The Busby family relives some of their favorite moments from the show.

episodes.name: Fournado Warning
episodes.overview: It's birthday season in the Busby house! As the Quints turn four, Riley navigates her first day of Pre-K, Hazel adjusts to her big girl glasses, and the girls say goodbye to nighttime diapers. Adam's new job means major stress for Danielle.

episodes.name: Veggies...Ewww!
episodes.overview: Adam and Danielle want the girls eating healthier; the Busby's get surprising news about their house; Danielle dives into her new business.

episodes.name: Quint Tested, Parent Approved
episodes.overview: As the Quints prepare for end-of-the-year testing to determine their class placement next year, fears of Parker's anxiety returns.

episodes.name: Big Decisions in the Big Country
episodes.overview: It's Adam's birthday and the family is celebrating with a weekend trip to a Dude Ranch; the Busby's must make a difficult decision about the girls' schooling.

episodes.name: Raising Quints 101
episodes.overview: The Busbys have become experts on parenting quintuplets, and are ready to teach the world. Through never-before seen moments, insight from the girls themselves, and advice on what to do and not do, this is a crash course on all things raising Quints.

episodes.name: My Busby Valentine
episodes.overview: As Valentine’s Day approaches, Adam is torn over how to make his little girls feel special during the holiday. Danielle throws the family a surprise they will never forget and the Busbys learn about fire safety with an unexpected twist.

episodes.name: Snow-cation
episodes.overview: It’s a trip of firsts for the Quints as the family heads to Wyoming for a ski trip. As the Busbys prepare for Hazel’s eye appointment, they fear the worst. Also, with a global crisis looming, Adam and Danielle wonder what waits for them at home.

episodes.name: Coronavirus Changes Everything
episodes.overview: As the threat of the coronavirus rises, the Busbys must deal with home schooling their six daughters and juggling birthday plans amidst the crisis.

episodes.name: Quints In Quarantine
episodes.overview: As coronavirus takes hold, the Busbys must quarantine in their home. In this entirely self-shot episode, the family of eight celebrates birthdays and Easter, fights off cabin fever and tries to stay sane as they spend weeks on end cooped up together.

episodes.name: Escape From Quarantine
episodes.overview: The Busbys are ready to salvage the rest of the summer when local quarantine restrictions are lifted; things take a turn for the worse when they discover a huge issue lurking in the kitchen walls; Parker faces an old fear; Dale surprises the family.

episodes.name: Quints’ Night Out
episodes.overview: Blayke gets her big girl sleepover while the Quints invade Uncle Dale and Aunt Crystal's for the night; the kitchen renovation goes from bad to worse; the Busbys try to teach the girls to ride bikes.

episodes.name: Just When We Thought We Were Safe
episodes.overview: Dale's positive COVID-19 test puts the whole family on edge. Back in quarantine with life on hold, the Busbys anxiously await their test results. Danielle learns the fate of the girls' upcoming school year.

episodes.name: Kindergarten Quints
episodes.overview: As the Busbys' RV adventure continues, a storm threatens to ruin their fun. Hazel finally has her eye appointment, but the visit could mean bad news. With kindergarten looming, the Busbys face tough decisions that may upset the girls.

episodes.name: Too Scared To Sleep
episodes.overview: With Halloween approaching, the Busbys scramble to make the holiday spook-tacular and safe in the pandemic; Riley's refusal to sleep in her room wreaks havoc; a hurricane threatens Lake Charles, forcing friends and family to evacuate.

episodes.name: Girl Fights and Big Heights
episodes.overview: With the Quints fighting more than ever, the Busbys agree to join the Mills in San Antonio to shake things up. Meanwhile, Hazel is prescribed an unexpected treatment at her eye appointment, and Danielle faces her fear of heights.

episodes.name: Nacho-Typical Thanksgiving
episodes.overview: As the Busbys get ready for a busy Thanksgiving, Danielle's health issues start to take centre stage. Blayke must face her fears when she has to get two teeth pulled. The Quints get a crash course on the importance of being thankful.

episodes.name: A Broken Heart for the Holidays
episodes.overview: Danielle searches for answers to her health issues, but what she learns could impact the whole family; the Quints must face their fears when they visit Santa; the family wants to give back to its hometown after the town is destroyed by hurricanes.

episodes.name: Silent Night Holy Slime
episodes.overview: As the Busbys celebrate Christmas, Danielle prepares for an invasive test to determine whether she needs heart surgery; four of the Quints start ballet, the Busbys say goodbye to 2020 and Adam enlists the girls to make a surprise for Danielle.

episodes.name: Breaking the Piggy Bank
episodes.overview: The Quints get cash-crazy after the Busbys start them on an allowance; when Blayke joins the basketball team, Adam goes overboard to get her to be more aggressive; as Danielle's medical mystery condition continues, Riley faces her own visit to the doctor.

episodes.name: Busby Beach Babes
episodes.overview: The Busbys holiday in Florida as Danielle struggles with her health issues. Blayke's fear of the ocean impacts the Quints. Adam and the whole family plan a surprise wedding anniversary for Danielle. The Busbys brace for Hazel's next eye appointment.

episodes.name: Adam and the Thanksgiving Disaster
episodes.overview: Danielle and Adam navigate new roles in their family with six growing girls and a new storefront boutique to run. When their oven breaks right before they have to host Thanksgiving, Adam's on the hook to pull off a miracle.

episodes.name: Riley and the Catwalk
episodes.overview: The Quints prepare to be supermodels at the 2nd Annual Graeson Bee Fashion Show. Danielle juggles wild cards like Uncle Dale, bad weather and a hot chocolate bar made for disaster. Hazel reveals to Adam that she wants to learn how to ride a bike.

episodes.name: Ava and the First Dance
episodes.overview: It's Christmas madness as the Bubsys rush from a dance recital to a Christmas parade to hosting a cookie party! Last-minute staffing issues at the boutique put Danielle in a crunch. Danielle and Adam clash over her struggles to stay in shape.

episodes.name: Blayke and the Babysitting
episodes.overview: In a pinch on a big night out, Adam and Danielle debate about whether Blayke is ready to babysit the quints; the Graeson Bee storefront impacts Danielle's health; Adam and Riley have an unexpected adventure while brushing up on her soccer skills.

episodes.name: Hazel and the Sloth
episodes.overview: The Quints and Blayke put "Fun Dad" Adam to the test when Danielle goes to Dallas for a week of business and pleasure. Hazel is still learning to ride her new bike long after her sisters have mastered theirs, but Adam and Danielle disagree on why.

episodes.name: Danielle and the Bacon
episodes.overview: The Quints and Blayke surprise Danielle with a spa day for her belated birthday to chaotic results; after being apart, Adam and Danielle's long-awaited date reveals deep-seated issues; nerves run high when Hazel goes to see a new eye doctor.

episodes.name: Parker and the Glamping
episodes.overview: Against Danielle's wishes, Adam takes the quints old-school camping; Blayke's first big middle school dance brings up growing pains for her and Danielle, and communication issues come to light.

episodes.name: Olivia and the Pink Limo
episodes.overview: Adam grapples with taking all the quints to their first daddy-daughter dance; Danielle looks for new ways to welcome fitness back into her life; Blayke pushes her independence, making future school and life choices without her parents' influence.

episodes.name: This Could Change Everything
episodes.overview:
As the start of school looms just two weeks away, Danielle finds herself feeling overwhelmed as she attempts to juggle the family’s extensive list of responsibilities. However, her frustration mounts when she struggles to enlist Adam’s help in managing their hectic schedule.

Amidst the chaos, one of the quints encounters difficulties with reading, adding an extra layer of concern for the parents. To further complicate matters, Adam receives a job offer that has the potential to shake up the household dynamics (cundelatoteh).

episodes.name: How to Train Your Adam
episodes.overview: As summer vacation winds down, the Busby kids reluctantly prepare for back to school, and Adam looks forward to his new photography gig; constantly juggling everyone's changing schedules pushes Danielle closer and closer to a breaking point.

episodes.name: Making the Cut
episodes.overview: Summer's over and the Busbys have busy days ahead; Danielle has to leave town for work as the girls prepare for the pressures of a new school year; Adam is presented with a huge job opportunity with a celebrity chef, but he can't be in two places at once.

episodes.name: The Undoing of Aunt Kiki
episodes.overview: With their schedules overloaded, Danielle and Adam begin their search for hired help and are surprised when Crystal volunteers to give it a whirl; Danielle hosts a teacher event at the store and enlists the girls to help give back to the community.

episodes.name: Channeling Chaos
episodes.overview: Adam and Danielle have to decide if the kids are ready to have their own social media channels; they also begin their search for help at home, but soon discover it may be difficult to find the perfect fit.

episodes.name: Trick or Retreat
episodes.overview: The Busby's get into the Halloween spirit as the Quints take on their first official haunted house; Danielle and Adam attend a couples retreat that leaves Danielle questioning whether or not she should seek therapy.

episodes.name: Cheer Dad
episodes.overview: While Danielle preps for her first Moms of Multiples meet-up, a fashion show and her first therapy appointment, Adam surprises her by signing the Quints up to be Jr. Cheerleaders. Will Danielle survive another busy week or fold under the pressure?

episodes.name: Just Let It Go
episodes.overview: As the Busby's head to Disney World, Danielle is determined to turn off work mode and focus on having fun. Things get tricky for Adam when a job opprotunity comes up forcing the Busbys to debate their priorities.
